Package gui

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PromotionListener
    A listener for handling a promotion
    SetPositionFrame.TileListenerHandle
    A handle to the tile listeners that is used to detach the listener from the board tiles when the set up board frame is closed
    TurnHappenedListener
    A listener interface for handling the event of a user having made a move (used when playing against a chess engine)
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    App
    Class containing main method.
    BoardCoordinate
    A class representing a coordinate on the chess board.
    BoardUtilities
    A helper class for finding out information about the current chess board position
    ChessBoard
    A class for showing the chessBoard, the pieces and allowing the user to make moves on the board
    EngineWorker
    A class for reading the output of an external chess engine on a different thread (so as to not lock up the GUI)
    MainFrame
    The MainFrame class contains all the components of the application
    MovesLogTableModel
    The table model for displaying the move history
    PromotionDialog
    A Dialog allowing the user to promote a pawn to a legal piece
    SetPositionFrame
    The frame that is responsible for setting up a custom position on the board
    Tile
    A class representing a tile (square) on a chess board
    UciParser
    A class for parsing the UCI responses of a chess engine
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MainFrame.GameMode
    The states that the application can be in at any given point
    PlayerColour
    An enum representing the player colours in chess
